appointed to Homes England’s Board","public_updated_at":"2019-08-16T09:43:07Z","document_type":"press_release","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/four-new-members-appointed-to-homes-england-s-board","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/four-new-members-appointed-to-homes-england-s-board","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"1dee2ea5-2c8a-4317-8736-0042471ab1eb","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/four-new-members-appointed-to-homes-england-s-board","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/four-new-members-appointed-to-homes-england-s-board","links":{}}]},"description":"Mark Rennison, Olivia Scanlon, Sadie Morgan and Vanessa Murden join the Homes England Board.","details":{"body":"<p>Four new members have been appointed to the Board of Homes England, the government’s housing accelerator.</p>\n\n<p>Mark Rennison, Olivia Scanlon, Sadie Morgan and Vanessa Murden join the Homes England Board with immediate effect, increasing its gender diversity and boosting its resilience; taking its non-executive members from 6 to 10.</p>\n\n<p>Mark Rennison is the Finance Director for Nationwide Building Society. He said of his appointment:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p class=\"last-child\">I am delighted to join the Homes England Board and look forward to helping to deliver a sustainable strategy for the creation of more high-quality affordable housing across the country.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Olivia Scanlon is the Chief Operating Officer at Orchard Global Asset Management LLP. Of joining the Homes England Board, she said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p class=\"last-child\">Homes England has an incredibly forward looking, innovative approach to addressing the country’s affordable housing shortage and I am thrilled to have been given the opportunity to be involved.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Sadie Morgan is a founding director of architectural practice dRMM. She commented:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p class=\"last-child\">As part of the Board’s agenda to build more sustainable and high-quality houses, my energy will be focused on delivering homes for people and places. I understand how vital the role of Homes England is to help house our nation, and I am committed to ensuring we do so and to deliver a quality of life everyone deserves.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Vanessa Murden is the Chief Operating Officer for Lloyds Banking Group’s retail division. She said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p class=\"last-child\">I’m looking forward to joining the Homes England Board and working with the team to grow access to affordable housing.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2 id=\"about-the-new-board-members\">About the new Board members</h2>\n\n<h3 id=\"mark-rennison\">Mark Rennison</h3>\n\n<p>Mark is the Finance Director for Nationwide Building Society. He also chairs the subsidiary company at Nationwide which is managing the Oakfield project to build a new housing community in Swindon. Prior to joining Nationwide he worked for PwC for 25 years including spending time as an audit partner in their banking practice in London.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"olivia-scanlon\">Olivia Scanlon</h3>\n\n<p>Olivia has a background in financial services, where she has almost 20 years of experience in general finance and investment as well as real estate development finance.  She is currently the Chief Operating Officer at Orchard Global Asset Management LLP.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"sadie-morgan\">Sadie Morgan</h3>\n\n<p>Sadie is a founding director of leading architectural practice dRMM. Over her 25-year career she has advocated exemplary design and architecture. She is a Commissioner and Design Group Chair of the National Infrastructure Commission and is the London Mayor’s Design Advocate.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"vanessa-murden\">Vanessa Murden</h3>\n\n<p>Vanessa has extensive senior executive expertise within the financial services industry, including Travelex, Western Union and Lloyds. She is currently the Chief Operating Officer for Lloyds Banking Group’s retail division.</p>\n\n<div id=\"contact_c1f13fd8-9feb-4028-9323-7cb3383323b4\" class=\"contact\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Media enquiries</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n    \n      <div class=\"email-url-number\">\n      \n        <p class=\"email\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Email</span>\n          <a href=\"mailto:newsdesk@communities.gov.uk\" class=\"email\">newsdesk@communities.gov.uk</a>\n        </p>\n      \n      \n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Please use this number if you are a journalist wishing to speak to Press Office</span>\n          0303 444 1209\n        </p>\n      \n      </div>\n    \n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"contact_bfc00333-a9ee-4ca1-9d3c-432dbcdf4640\" class=\"contact postal-address\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Office address and general enquiries</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n      <p class=\"adr\">\n<span class=\"street-address\">2 Marsham Street\n<br>\nLondon</span><br>\n<span class=\"postal-code\">SW1P 4DF</span>\n</p>\n\n    \n    \n      <div class=\"email-url-number\">\n      \n      \n        <p class=\"contact_form_url\">\n          <span class=\"type\">Contact form</span>\n          <a href=\"https://forms.communities.gov.uk/\">https://forms.communit...</a>\n        </p>\n      \n      \n        <p class=\"tel\">\n          <span class=\"type\">General enquiries:  please use this number if you are a member of the public</span>\n          030 3444 0000\n        </p>\n      \n      </div>\n    \n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"contact_f375ee5c-c7f3-4e09-9ba8-2ca0308481c5\" class=\"contact\">\n  <div class=\"content\">\n    <h3>Social media - MHCLG</h3>\n    <div class=\"vcard contact-inner\">\n    \n    \n    \n      <p class=\"comments\">Twitter - <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mhclg\">https://twitter.com/mhclg</a><br>Flickr - <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/mhclg\">http://www.flickr.com/photos/mhclg</a><br>LinkedIn - <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/company/mhclg\">http://www.linkedin.com/company/mhclg</a></p>\n    \n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-08-16T09:06:05.569Z"}]},"document_status":"published_but_needs_2i","created_by":"Wolfgang Güllick","last_updated_by":"Junko Tabei","political":true,"government":{"title":"2015 Conservative government","slug":"2015-conservative-government","start_date":"2015-05-07T23:00:00.000Z","end_date":"","current":true}}